members.member:
Contains all the settings for parsing structures.
The setting are given by enumerated flags at construction, making instances immutable.
Functions are available to reinterpret these settings when applied to parsing XML structures into Objects.
The StructureSettings take into account two settings for parsing SDMX-ML documents
Resolve Cross References
Resolve External References
Cross References are declared by structures such as Key Families also known as a Data Structure Definition (DSD) (see DataStructureObject). A DSD contains a number of Dimensions (IDimension) a Dimensions may declare a reference to a Codelist and a Concept through reference parameters.
If a system is to resolve the cross references, then it can do this by either of the following ways:
Resolve the external reference exists at the given URI
Resolve the external reference exists, and substitute it for the provided 'stub' artifact
Either of the above two can be lenient (do not error if it can not be done) or not (throw exception if this could not be done)
External References are declared by MaintainableObject structures by having their isExternal attribute set to true. In this instance the Maintainable artifact is declaring that it is not the full artifact, but just an empty container whose purpose is to declare the existence of the artifact (stub). The stub also has the responsibility of declaring where to get the full artifact, this is defined by the URI attribute.
The StructureSettings provides the following options for resolving cross references:
Do not resolve
Resolve all the references (it is up to the implementation to decide how deep to resolve)
Resolve all the references except for Agencies
External references are when a structure is declared, like a codelist, as a 'stub' containing the minimum possible information for it to be valid against the schema; i.e it has a name, id and agency id, but it also has a URI which says: if you want the full codelists, with a 100 million codes, it's retrievable from this location. This is useful if someone wants to store information in the registry, but maintain the contents of the artifacts externally.
which is built from an XML message.
which is built from resolving all the cross referenced artifacts.

member.name: T:Org.Sdmxsource.Sdmx.Api.Model.Objects.Base.ISdmxObject
member.summary:
An SdmxObject represents any SDMX structural artefact or metadata structure artefact
All classes which inherit from SdmxObject are immutable, meaning they can not have any of their contents modified. Any collections returned as a result of a method call will be copies of collections ensuring the immutability of the SdmxObject is preserved. This 'copy paradigm' is also true of composite objects returned, which are mutable, for example any object of type will be a copy of the underlying Date object contained in the SDXMObject.

member.name: T:Org.Sdmxsource.Sdmx.Api.Model.Objects.Base.IMaintainableObject
member.summary:
A IMaintainableObject is a top level Object (contains no parents), it has a reference to an Agency getAgencyId() and has a mandatory id and a mandatory version, defaulting to 1.0.
The unique identifier of a maintainable artefact is the AgencyId, Id and Version.
Each maintainable artefact can create a mutable representation of itself (getMutableInstance()) and can also return a stub representation of itself getStub().

member.name: T:Org.Sdmxsource.Sdmx.Api.Model.Objects.Base.IConstrainableObject
member.summary:
A constrainable @object is one which can have constraints associated with it.
Constraints are not `by composition` but `by reference` therefore a constraint can only reference a constrainable artifact, a constrainable artifact does not contain the constraint.

member.name: P:Org.Sdmxsource.Sdmx.Api.Model.Objects.Base.IConstrainableObject.CrossReferencedConstrainables
member.summary:
Gets the cross referenced constrainables.
Registration would return reference to a provision agreement
Provision Agreement would return a reference to a dataflow and a Data Provider
Dataflow would return a reference to a data structure
Data Structure would return null (example a provision agreement would return a reference to a dataflow)

member.name: T:Org.Sdmxsource.Sdmx.Api.Model.Objects.DataStructure.IDataStructureObject
member.summary:
A Data Structure also known as a Data Structure Definition (DSD) or KeyFamily describes the dimensionality of the data.
A Data Structure contains Dimensions, Attributes, Groups, and a Measure. Each of these components is held in its respective identifiable list container (DimensionList, AttributeList, MeasureList), however the DataStructureObject exposes the methods to obtain the Dimensions, Attributes, Measure, and Groups without having to navigate through the list.

member.name: T:Org.Sdmxsource.Sdmx.Api.Engine.IDataWriterEngine
member.summary:
A DataWriterEngine has the ability to write data to a given location in a given format based on the calls to the methods provided.
The Data Format that is written out depends on the implementation of the DataWriter.
The output location also depends on the implementation of the DataWriter

member.name: M:Org.Sdmxsource.Sdmx.Api.Engine.IDataWriterEngine.Close(Org.Sdmxsource.Sdmx.Api.Model.IFooterMessage[])
member.summary:
Writes the footer message (if supported by the writer implementation), and then completes the XML document, closes off all the tags, closes any resources. NOTE It is very important to close off a completed DataWriterEngine, as this ensures any output is written to the given location, and any resources are closed. If this call is not made, the output document may be incomplete.
NOTE: If writing a footer is not supported, then the footer will be silently ignored
Close also validates that the last series key or group key has been completed.
Starts a dataset with the data conforming to the DSD
member.param: Optional. The dataflow can be provided to give extra information about the dataset.
The data structure is used to know the dimenisonality of the data

Datset header containing, amongst others, the dataset action, reporting dates, dimension at observation if null then the dimension at observation is assumed to be TIME_PERIOD and the dataset action is assumed to be INFORMATION
Any additional annotations that are attached to the dataset, can be null if no annotations exist
member.exception: if the dsd is null

member.name: M:Org.Sdmxsource.Sdmx.Api.Engine.IDataWriterEngine.StartGroup(System.String,Org.Sdmxsource.Sdmx.Api.Model.Objects.Base.IAnnotation[])
member.param: Annotations any additional annotations that are attached to the group, can be null if no annotations exist

member.name: M:Org.Sdmxsource.Sdmx.Api.Engine.IDataWriterEngine.StartSeries(Org.Sdmxsource.Sdmx.Api.Model.Objects.Base.IAnnotation[])
member.summary: Starts a new series, closes off any existing series keys or attribute/observations.
member.param: Any additional annotations that are attached to the series, can be null if no annotations exist

member.name: M:Org.Sdmxsource.Sdmx.Api.Engine.IDataWriterEngine.WriteAttributeValue(System.String,System.String)
member.summary:
Writes an attribute value for the given id.
If this method is called immediately after a writeSeriesKeyValue method call then it will write the attribute at the series level. If it is called after a writeGroupKeyValue it will write the attribute against the group.
If this method is called immediately after a writeObservation method call then it will write the attribute at the observation level.
member.param: the id of the given value for example 'OBS_STATUS'

member.name: M:Org.Sdmxsource.Sdmx.Api.Engine.IDataWriterEngine.WriteGroupKeyValue(System.String,System.String)
member.summary:
Writes a group key value, for example 'Country' is 'France'. A group may contain multiple id/value pairs in the key, so this method may be called consecutively with an id / value for each key item.
If this method is called consecutively multiple times and a duplicate id is passed in, then an exception will be thrown, as a group can only declare one value for a given id.
The startGroup method must be called before calling this method to add the first id/value, as the WriterEngine needs to know what group to assign the id/values to.
member.param: the id of the concept or dimension

member.name: M:Org.Sdmxsource.Sdmx.Api.Engine.IDataWriterEngine.WriteObservation(System.String,System.String,Org.Sdmxsource.Sdmx.Api.Model.Objects.Base.IAnnotation[])
member.summary: Writes an observation, the observation concept is assumed to be that which has been defined to be at the observation level (as declared in the start dataset method DatasetHeaderObject).
member.param: May be the observation time, or the cross section value
The observation value - can be numerical
Any additional annotations that are attached to the observation, can be null if no annotations exist

member.name: M:Org.Sdmxsource.Sdmx.Api.Engine.IDataWriterEngine.WriteObservation(System.String,System.String,System.String,Org.Sdmxsource.Sdmx.Api.Model.Objects.Base.IAnnotation[])
member.summary:
Writes an Observation value against the current series.
The current series is determined by the latest writeKeyValue call, If this is a cross sectional dataset, then the obsConcept is expected to be the cross sectional concept value - for example if this is cross sectional on Country the id may be "FR" If this is a time series dataset then the obsConcept is expected to be the observation time - for example 2006-12-12
Validates the following:
The obsTime string format is one of an allowed SDMX time format
The obsTime does not replicate a previously reported obsTime for the current series
member.param: the concept id for the observation, for example 'COUNTRY'. If this is a Time Series, then the id will be DimensionBean.TIME_DIMENSION_FIXED_ID.
may be the observation time, or the cross section value
The observation value - can be numerical
Any additional annotations that are attached to the observation, can be null if no annotations exist

member.name: M:Org.Sdmxsource.Sdmx.Api.Engine.IDataWriterEngine.WriteObservation(System.DateTime,System.String,Org.Sdmxsource.Sdmx.Api.Constants.TimeFormat,Org.Sdmxsource.Sdmx.Api.Model.Objects.Base.IAnnotation[])
member.summary:
Writes an Observation value against the current series
The date is formatted as a string, the format rules are determined by the TIME_FORMAT argument
Validates the following:
The obsTime does not replicate a previously reported obsTime for the current series
member.param: the observation value - can be numerical
the time format to format the obsTime in when converting to a string

member.name: M:Org.Sdmxsource.Sdmx.Api.Engine.IDataWriterEngine.WriteSeriesKeyValue(System.String,System.String)
member.summary:
Writes a series key value. This will have the effect of closing off any observation, or attribute values if they are any present
If this method is called after calling writeAttribute or writeObservation, then the engine will start a new series.
member.param: the id of the value for example 'Country'

Observations that have been added since the last time the query was performed (INSERT)
Observations that have been revised since the last time the query was performed (UPDATE)

member.name: T:Org.Sdmxsource.Sdmx.Api.Model.Metadata.IReferenceValue
member.summary:

member.name: T:Org.Sdmxsource.Sdmx.Api.Manager.Parse.IStructureVersionIncrementManager
member.summary:
Increments the version of any maintainable beans if the bean already exists. The rules are:
If the beans contains a structure that does not yet exist in no action is taken
If the structure already exists then the version number of the SdmxBeans structure is incremented, meaning the existing structure remains unchanged
A minor version increment is performed if the structure does differ in the identifiable composite structures. For example, a codelist with exactly the same codes (a code is identifiable as it has a URN)
A major increment is performed if the submitted structure has an additional identifiable or has had an identifiable removed. For example a codelist may have had a code removed
A minor version increment is a .1 increase. For example 1.2 becomes 1.3 (or 1.3.2 becomes 1.4)
A major version increment is a full integer increase. For example version 1.0 becomes 2.0 (or 1.4 becomes 2.0)
Any structures which cross reference the existing structure will also have a minor version increment and the references will be updated to reference the latest structure. This rule is recursive, so any structures that reference the references are also updated. This rule will also apply if the referencing document is the same structure submission, as long as the referencing structure in the submission has had the reference modified

member.name: M:Org.Sdmxsource.Sdmx.Api.Manager.Parse.IStructureVersionIncrementManager.IncrementVersions(Org.Sdmxsource.Sdmx.Api.Model.Objects.ISdmxObjects)
member.summary: Processes the SdmxBeans to determine if any already exist. If they do then it will determine if there are any changes to the structure, if there are then the submitted structure will have it's version number automatically incremented.
